    <h2>Headings in HTML</h2>
    <p>
        Headings are like the titles of a story — they range from <b>&lt;h1&gt;</b> (largest) 
        to <b>&lt;h6&gt;</b> (smallest). They help structure and organize information clearly.
    </p>

    <h2>About Me - Heading 1</h2>
    <h3>Education - Heading 2</h3>
    <h4>Interests - Heading 3</h4>
    <h5>Goals - Heading 4</h5>
    <h6>Motivation - Heading 5</h6>
    <h2>Paragraphs</h2>
    <p>
        I’m pursuing <b>B.Tech in CSE (AI/ML Specialization)</b> at <i>Rungta College, Bhilai</i>.  
        My interests include <u>web development</u>, <u>machine learning</u>, and 
        <i>creative coding</i> that solves real-life challenges.
    </p>

    <h2>Text Formatting Tags</h2>
    <p><b>Bold:</b> Coding gives me confidence.</p>
    <p><strong>Strong:</strong> I believe smart work creates success.</p>
    <p><i>Italic:</i> I enjoy learning new programming concepts.</p>
    <p><u>Underline:</u> Focus and dedication define my path.</p>
    <p><mark>Highlighted:</mark> “Artificial Intelligence is the future.”</p>
    <p>Chemical Formula Example: Na<sub>2</sub>CO<sub>3</sub></p>
    <p>Math Expression Example: (a + b)<sup>2</sup> = a<sup>2</sup> + 2ab + b<sup>2</sup></p>

    <h2>Conclusion</h2>
    <p>
        This page demonstrates the basic use of <b>HTML headings, paragraphs,</b> 
        and <b>text formatting</b> through a creative introduction about <strong>Naitik kumar</strong>.
        Every tag here represents my journey — <i>simple, structured, and meaningful.</i>
